examples.en: The day declined.
I invited him, but he declined.
She declined to address the delegates.
Profits declined by 10%.
Mary declined Jay's invitation to dinner.
I declined an upgrade to business class.
He declined engaging himself to secrecy.
He changed his mind and declined the company's offer.
The standard of work has declined.
Car sales have declined by a quarter.
The court declined to review her case.
They declined even to consider the idea.
He declined to join the group on a hike.
Crime rates have declined in recent years.
The company declined comment on the scandal.
Cinemas declined with the growth of television.
After the war, the city declined in importance.
Mary declined a hot drink and went to her room.
Spending on information technology has declined.
The president's popularity has declined considerably.
Undoubtedly, public interest in folk music has declined.
When asked for details, he declined to elucidate further.
He declined to make projections about fourth quarter earnings.
The construction of new houses declined five percent this year.
Trade Union membership declined by 5% over the last five years.
A spokesman declined to comment until the evidence could be studied further.
Offered the position of chairman, Smith declined, preferring to keep his current job.
The rate of population growth reached a peak in 1999 and declined in subsequent years.
The birth rate for older women has declined, but, by contrast, births to teenage mothers have increased.
